=Here is the code for conda=

 * *conda info --envs* # Check for the current env
 * *conda deactivate* # Deactivate the env
 * *conda activate myDjangoEnv* # Activate the env_named


==How to create a new envirurment==
- In terminal type

{{{
conda create -n env_name pyhton=x.x
}}}

- The terminal will ask for installing several libraries
- Choose yes [y]

=== Install the requirments ===

- In terminal cd to the directory that contains the requirments.txt
- In terminal type the code

{{{
pip3 install -r requirments.txt 
}}}







